post_content:
Brief list of Easter activities.

  • Church (a bit earlier than normal.. though it hopefully will help me get back onto a better sleep schedule)
  • Hanging out at my aunt's place with my Mom's side of the family (my mom came down from Rochester as well, good to see her)
  • Caught up a bit Wit James (haven't talked to him since he got to go to Hawaii for work.. yea Hawaii, for work, tough life :))
  • Watched most of the The Incredibles again (second time in a week, but still not old. I need to get that DVD)
  • Ate lots, the homemade creme-puffs were particularly magnificent (thanks Erin!)
  • Played poker (no limit hold'em of course) and did pretty well (though we never got the chance to finish, I was chipleader with 3 players left when we stopped)
  • Watched the suspense filled ending of the Kentucky vs Michigan State game (though Kentucky fell apart in the second overtime)
  • Came home and worked on the photography presentation I should have done more on over spring break.
  • Going to bed early.. (well early if you call 1:00am early)
